The paper deals with the application of machine learning algorithms to automate the classification of marine benthic biota from image data collected by autonomous underwater vehicles. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of deep residual networks for feature extraction, which is a popular technique in machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG). The use of autonomous underwater vehicles for data collection involves robotics and control (cs.RO). Finally, the paper also discusses the application of the proposed method to study the change in kelp cover over time, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR).
